  "prompt": "What are good watches for men under $200?",
  "response": "There are many great options for men's watches under $200 that combine style, reliability, and functionality. Here are some popular choices:\n\n1. **Seiko 5 Automatic** - Known for its durability and automatic movement, this watch is a classic choice that offers great value.\n\n2. **Casio G-Shock** - Famous for its toughness and durability, G-Shock offers a range of styles and features, including water resistance and shock resistance.\n\n3. **Timex Weekender** - A versatile and casual watch, the Weekender features interchangeable straps and a minimalist design, making it perfect for everyday wear.\n\n4. **Citizen Eco-Drive** - Citizen's Eco-Drive technology uses light to power the watch, so you never need to replace the battery. There are several stylish models available under $200.\n\n5. **Fossil Gen 5E Smartwatch** - For those looking for smartwatch features, the Fossil Gen 5E offers fitness tracking and notifications while maintaining a classic watch aesthetic.\n\n6. **Orient Bambino** - This dress watch offers an elegant and classic look with a variety of dial colors, all while being powered by a reliable automatic movement.\n\n7. **Bulova Classic Automatic** - This watch features a sophisticated design with an automatic movement at an accessible price point.\n\n8. **Timex Ironman Classic 30** - A great option for athletes, this digital watch is water-resistant and has features like a stopwatch and countdown timer.\n\n9. **Invicta Pro Diver** - This offers a bold dive watch appearance at a fraction of the price of luxury brands, with various styles available.\n\n10. **St\u00fchrling Original** - Offers unique designs with skeleton and automatic options that stand out without breaking the bank.\n\nWhen choosing a watch, consider your personal style, the occasions you'll wear it for, and any specific features you want (like water resistance, smart features, or automatic movement).",
